Module com.example.sudoku
Package com.example.sudoku.model.board

Class Board

java.lang.Object
com.example.sudoku.model.board.Board
All Implemented Interfaces:
IBoard
public class Board extends Object implements IBoard
This class represents a 6x6 Sudoku board and provides methods to initialize, validate, and manipulate the board. It includes functionality to generate a valid Sudoku puzzle, check for valid moves, provide hints, and track move history.

  • Method Details

    • initializeBoard

      public void initializeBoard()
      Initializes the Sudoku board by generating a valid puzzle with a reasonable difficulty level. The method first fills the board with zeros, then creates a complete valid Sudoku solution. It then removes numbers from the board while ensuring that each 2x3 grid has at least two visible cells, and adds some extra visible cells to achieve a reasonable difficulty level

    • getHint

      public int getHint(int row, int col)
      Provides a hint for a specific cell by returning the correct value that should be placed in that cell. If the cell is already filled, it returns 0. It uses the Sudoku solver to find a completed solution and retrieves the value for the specified cell.
      Parameters:
      row -
      col -
      Returns:

    • getSomeHint

      public int[] getSomeHint()
      Provides a hint for one of the empty cells on the board by randomly selecting an empty cell and returning its row, column, and the correct value to be placed there. If no empty cells are available or no valid hint can be found, it returns null

    • undoLastMove

      public void undoLastMove()
      Undoes the last move made on the board by reverting the cell to its previous value. If there are no moves in the history, the method does nothing.
